text: The Senegalese Football Federation (; FSF) is the governing body of football in Senegal. It is in charge of the men's and the women's national teams. The association was founded in 1960. It became a member of FIFA in 1964 and CAF in 1963. It is based in the capital Dakar. Category:1960 establishments in Africa Category:Football governing bodies in Africa Category:Sport in Senegal
title: Senegalese Football Federation
